\begin{table}
\captionsetup{labelformat=empty}
\caption{Table 197 Entry types in Sentaurus Device (Continued)}
\begin{tabular}{|l|l|}
\hline Entry type & Description \\
\hline Vector & \begin{tabular}{l}
Vectors in real space are defined depending on the actual dimension as follows: \\
- In three dimensions, a vector is specified by three floating-point numbers. \\
- In two dimensions, a vector is specified by two floating-point numbers enclosed in parentheses. The floating-point numbers are separated by commas or space. \\
- In one dimension, one floating-point number without parentheses is sufficient. \\
Valid vectors are \((1,0,2)\), \((1 \mathrm{e}-4,-1 \mathrm{e}-3)\), and 1.
\end{tabular} \\
\hline String & Strings are delimited by quotation marks. They are compatible with the C language format for strings. The following strings are valid: "Vdd", "output/diode" \\
\hline Identifier & These are used to name objects such as nodes, devices, or attributes. They are compatible with the C language format for identifiers. The following identifiers are valid: vdd, diode, bjt_345 \\
\hline Assignment & These are used to set values to keywords. Therefore, the following are valid assignments: Digits=4, Save="output/diode" \\
\hline Signal & Signals are time dependent, piecewise, linear functions (not to be confused with UNIX signals) that are defined as inputs on the contacts of a device. They are specified as follows: (value0 at time0, value1 at time1, ...value_n at time_n). The following signal is valid: ( 0 at 0,1 at \(10.0 \mathrm{e}-9,1\) at \(20.0 \mathrm{e}-9\) ) \\
\hline List & \begin{tabular}{l}
Lists are collections of keywords, assignments, and complex entries. They are delimited by " (...) " or " \(\{\ldots\}\) ". The following lists are valid: \\
\{ Number \(=0\) Voltage=0 \\
Voltage \(=(0\) at 0,0 at \(2 \mathrm{e}-8\) ) \} \\
\{ Method=Super Digits=6 Numerically \} \\
( MinStep=1e-15 InitialStep=1e-10 Digits=3 )
\end{tabular} \\
\hline Structured entries & These are parameterized definitions or commands that can have the forms <keyword> \{<keywords>\},<keyword> (<keywords>), or <keyword> (<list>) \{<list>\}. \\
\hline
\end{tabular}
\end{table}

